1.0.0-23 | 2025-02-08 13:20:13 -0700

  * Wrap function bodies in `when` conditions (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

    This reverses checking for when before defining the functions to
    instead putting the when condition inside the function body. I
    grepped around the el files that come with emacs and this appears
    to be the standard form.

    This also fixes some of the function comments to include the
    argument names like they should.

  * Add autoload and sharp-quote hints for the byte-compiler (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Mark a couple of functions as private (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Remove undefined c-basic-offset (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

    We're not requiring c-mode to be loaded, so this variable won't be
    defined. We don't want to load all of c-mode just for this one
    variable either.

  * Require whitespace package for whitespace-mode (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Fix formatting of apostrophes in comments (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Remove commented-out keymapping (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Update license file to match the main Zeek file (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Remove extra 'provide' statement (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Closing parens shouldn't be on lines alone (emacs lisp style-guide) (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Use spaces for all indentation (emacs lisp style-guide) (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

  * Initial pass over docs with 'checkdoc' (Tim Wojtulewicz, Corelight)

